3.  PORE FLUIDS 
 
3.1   Pore-Fluid Composition 
3.1.1  Three varieties of pore solutions infill sediment pores: meteoric, 
connate, and juvenile (Figure 7-6).  Meteoric water originates from the 
precipitation or rain and snow from the atmosphere.  Connate water has evolved 
from the original water associated with deposition, and juvenile waters are of 
magmatic origin. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
