The solubility of calcite and silica are unaffected by Eh but are strongly affected—
and in opposing ways—by pH.  Silica solubility increases with pH, whereas 
calcite solubility decreases with pH.  Thus in acidic pore fluids, like meteoric 
waters, calcite tends to dissolve and quartz overgrowths are precipitated, whereas 
